Media notes: Downy Woodpecker nest with young calling. Using the ME 66 with out a wind cover. Mic was on a boom and held at the nest entrance. The parents were calling from trees near the nest and the young became quiet until I placed the mic in the nest hole entrance. Equipment Notes: Recorder's HPF on (80Hz, -18dB/octave). Elevation: 176 m.

Locality: Tijuana River Valley--Bird & Butterfly Garden (Myers Ranch)

Media notes: Drumming on a dead aspen. Two other birds landed nearby and had an aggressive encounter and this bird gave a hoarser rattle (5:48).

Locality: Trails west of Bird & Butterfly area (32.554, -117.089)

Media notes: Drumming and call by female Downy Woodpecker.  Photo is of the recorded bird.

Downy Woodpecker nest with young calling. Using the ME 66 with the Rycote SuperSoftie wind cover. Mic was on a boom and held at the nest entrance. Touching the nest entrance caused the young to increase their calling rate. At one point one of the young gives a loud alarm call that brought in both parents. Equipment Notes: Recorder's HPF on (80Hz, -18dB/octave). Elevation: 176 m.

Background Species: Setophaga pinus -- Pine Warbler; Larus delawarensis -- Ring-billed Gull
Media notes: Female adult calling and foraging in a tree.
One called near me then another called (same descending call) from other side of Bald Eagle Creek (though I don't think you can hear it in the recording).
